The paper deals with the construction of tree covers and Ramsey tree covers, which are important in algorithmic applications such as routing and distance oracles. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper also focuses on planar and doubling metrics, which are common in computational geometry, indicating that it may also belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The study of distortion and the number of trees required for good coverings suggests that the paper may also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on the construction of coverings suggests that it may also belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category.
